2010, Pattinson was named by ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine as one of the [[Time 100|100 most influential people in the world]], and he was featured in the [[Forbes Celebrity 100]] list.<ref name=\"time\">{{Cite news |author=Chris Weitz |title=The 2010 Time 100: Robert Pattinson |url=http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,1984685_1984940_1984948,00.html#ixzz0mUOIhqVr |work=Time |date=29 April 2010 |accessdate=2 May 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100502133329/http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,1984685_1984940_1984948,00.html#ixzz0mUOIhqVr |archive-date=2 May 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"forbes1\">{{cite news|title=The Celebrity 100: No.50 Robert Pattinson|url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2010/53/celeb-100-10_Robert-Pattinson_TZ0B.html|work=Forbes|date=28 June 2010|access-date=10 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170930042721/https://www.forbes.com/lists/2010/53/celeb-100-10_Robert-Pattinson_TZ0B.html|archive-date=30 September 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On 14 November 2010, Pattinson received two BBC Radio 1 Teen Awards, Best Dressed and Best Actor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/pressoffice/pressreleases/stories/2010/11_november/15/teen.shtml|title=Radio 1's Teen Awards winners announced|work=BBC|date=15 November 2010|accessdate=15 March 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101118101128/http://www.bbc.co.uk/pressoffice/pressreleases/stories/2010/11_november/15/teen.shtml|archive-date=18 November 2010|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, Pattinson was 15th on ''Vanity Fair''{{-'}}s \"Hollywood Top 40\" with earnings of $27.5&nbsp;million in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/features/2011/03/hollywood-top-earners-201103?currentPage=3|title=Hollywood's Top 40|work=Vanity Fair|first=Peter|last=Newcomb|date=March 2011|accessdate=15 March 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120413212910/http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/features/2011/03/hollywood-top-earners-201103?currentPage=3|archivedate=13 April 2012}}</ref> ''GQ'' once again named Pattinson the \"Best Dressed Man\" of 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=Robert Pattinson: GQ Best Dressed Man 2012|url=http://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/style/articles/2012-03/02/best-dressed-men-voting-results/robert-pattinson#ContentTop|work=GQ|accessdate=6 March 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120308202036/http://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/style/articles/2012-03/02/best-dressed-men-voting-results/robert-pattinson#ContentTop|archivedate=8 March 2012}}</ref> In October 2012, Pattinson was named \"Sexiest Man Alive\" by ''[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour UK]]''.<ref>{{cite web|author=Maria Vultaggio|title=Robert Pattinson is named 'Sexiest Man Alive', beating out other potential Christian Grey favorites|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/robert-pattinson-sexiest-man-alive-beating-out-other-potential-christian-grey-favorites-798617|work=[[International Business Times]]|date=1 October 2012|accessdate=14 October 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121006070918/http://www.ibtimes.com/robert-pattinson-sexiest-man-alive-beating-out-other-potential-christian-grey-favorites-798617|archive-date=6 October 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, Pattinson was 2nd on ''[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour UK]]''s \"Richest UK Celebs Under 30\" with earnings of \u00a345&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|title=Richest UK Celebs Under 30|url=http://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/celebrity/celebrity-galleries/2012/04/richest-uk-celebs-under-30-2012#!image-number=29|work=[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour UK]]|accessdate=26 June 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130503001453/http://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/celebrity/celebrity-galleries/2012/04/richest-uk-celebs-under-30-2012#!image-number=29|archive-date=3 May 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> Britain's [[London Evening Standard]] named him one of the ''London's most influential people of 2013'' in their ''The Power 1000''.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Power 1000 \u2013 London's most influential people 2013|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/london/the-power-1000--londons-most-influential-people-2013-imagineers-film-8825001.html|work=[[London Evening Standard]]|accessdate=23 October 2013|date=2013-09-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131030145929/http://www.standard.co.uk/news/london/the-power-1000--londons-most-influential-people-2013-imagineers-film-8825001.html|archive-date=30 October 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> In February 2014, he appeared on the cover of ''World Film Locations: Toronto'', a book about Toronto and the films shot in the city.<ref>{{cite book|title=World Film Locations: Toronto|url=http://press.uchicago.edu/ucp/books/book/distributed/W/bo18079552.html|work=press.uchicago|accessdate=18 February 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222152759/http://press.uchicago.edu/ucp/books/book/distributed/W/bo18079552.html|archive-date=22 February 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> A play about three mature women obsessed with Pattinson, titled ''Totally Devoted'', debuted at [[Surgeons' Hall|Surgeons' Hall, Edinburgh]] on 13 August 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=totally devoted|url=http://www.skiddle.com/whats-on/Edinburgh/-Surgeons%27-Hall/Totally-Devoted/12226007|work=skiddle|accessdate=13 August 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140813094721/http://www.skiddle.com/whats-on/Edinburgh/-Surgeons%27-Hall/Totally-Devoted/12226007/|archive-date=13 August 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> In October 2014, Pattinson was 3rd on ''[[Heat (magazine)|Heat magazine]]'''s \"annual rich list of young British stars\" with earnings of $82.89 million.<ref>{{cite web|title=One Direction Beat Out Daniel Radcliffe to Top U.K. Under 30 Rich List|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/one-direction-beat-daniel-radcliffe-742831|work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=22 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141025075320/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/one-direction-beat-daniel-radcliffe-742831|archive-date=25 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> London Evening Standard included him in their list of 2014's ''London's 1000 most influential people''.<ref>{{cite web|title=The 1000 - London's most influential people 2014: The Arts|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/the1000/the-1000--londons-most-influential-people-2014-the-arts-9784853.html|work=London Evening Standard|accessdate=15 December 2014|date=2014-10-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129045125/http://www.standard.co.uk/news/the1000/the-1000--londons-most-influential-people-2014-the-arts-9784853.html|archive-date=29 November 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nPattinson interviewed actor [[Jamie Bell]] for [[Interview (magazine)|Interview magazine]], which was published on 20 July 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.interviewmagazine.com/film/jamie-bell#_|title=JAMIE BELL By ROBERT PATTINSON|accessdate=20 July 2015|date=2015-07-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150721215248/http://www.interviewmagazine.com/film/jamie-bell#_|archive-date=21 July 2015|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn the summer of 2009, Pattinson became romantically linked to his ''[[The Twilight Saga (film series)|The Twilight Saga]]'' co-star [[Kristen Stewart]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.popsugar.co.uk/gdpr?gdpr|title=Robert Pattinson & Kristen Stewart seen kissing at Kings of Leon concert in Vancouver|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=}}</ref> In July 2012, Stewart was photographed having an affair with her ''[[Snow White and the Huntsman]]'' director, [[Rupert Sanders]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/kristen-stewart-cheats-on-robert-pattinson-with-rupert-sanders-see-all-of-the-shocking-pics-from-their-fling-2012307/|title=Kristen Cheats on Rob: See All the Shocking Pics!|date=30 July 2012|work=Us Weekly|access-date=11 August 2018|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180812021618/https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/kristen-stewart-cheats-on-robert-pattinson-with-rupert-sanders-see-all-of-the-shocking-pics-from-their-fling-2012307/|archive-date=12 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The day that the photos were released, Sanders, who was 19 years older than Stewart and married at the time, issued a public apology for the affair, as did Stewart.<ref>Jordan, Julie; Schwartz, Alison. [http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20614722,00.html \"Kristen Stewart's Apology to Robert Pattinson for Cheating\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/6EDx49RIs?url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20614722,00.html |date=6 February 2013 }}, ''People'', 25 July 2012; accessed 13 June 2014.</ref> Pattinson and Stewart split, but reconciled in October 2012. The pair eventually broke up in May 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=Robert Pattinson Moves Stuff Out of Kristen Stewart's House, Leaves With His Dogs|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/420886/robert-pattinson-moves-stuff-out-of-kristen-stewart-s-house-leaves-with-his-dogs|website=E Online|accessdate=29 September 2014|first=Natalie|last=Finn|date=20 May 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006150918/http://www.eonline.com/news/420886/robert-pattinson-moves-stuff-out-of-kristen-stewart-s-house-leaves-with-his-dogs|archive-date=6 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2014, Pattinson began dating singer [[FKA Twigs]]. They were rumored to be engaged, but never publicly confirmed it. The couple split in summer 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a13034508/robert-pattinson-fka-twigs-break-up-engagement|title=Robert Pattinson and FKA Twigs Have Officially Broken Up|website=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]|date=7 October 2017|accessdate=28 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327151400/https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a13034508/robert-pattinson-fka-twigs-break-up-engagement/|archive-date=27 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n[[File:Twilight cast imprints at Grauman's Chinese Theater.jpg|thumb|upright|Handprints, footprints and signatures of (from left to right) [[Taylor Lautner|Lautner]], [[Kristen Stewart|Stewart]] and Pattinson.]]\n{{main|List of awards and nominations received by Robert Pattinson}}\nPattinson has received Best Actor award at ''Strasbourg Film Festival'' for his performance in ''[[How to Be]]'' (2009).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.strasbourgfilmfest.com/films-up-for-nods-08.html |title=Strasbourg International Film Festival: 2008 Awards |website=Strasbourgfilmfest.com |accessdate=22 August 2010 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130409044743/http://www.strasbourgfilmfest.com/films-up-for-nods-08.html |archivedate=9 April 2013  }}</ref> For his work in ''[[The Twilight Saga (film series)|The Twilight Saga]]'', he has earned two [[Empire Award]]s nominations and won eleven [[MTV Movie & TV Awards|MTV Movie Awards]], two [[People's Choice Awards]] with additional other awards and nominations including winning 2009's Hollywood Film Award for New Hollywood by [[Hollywood Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hollywoodfest.com/2008/10/ben-stiller-marissa-tomei-among-this-years-honorees/|title=Ben Stiller & Marissa Tomei Among This Year's Honorees|website=hollywoodfest.com|accessdate=11 January 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130119213743/http://hollywoodfest.com/2008/10/ben-stiller-marissa-tomei-among-this-years-honorees/|archive-date=19 January 2013|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Jameson Empire Awards Announce 2009 Nominees |url=https://www.empireonline.com/awards2009/winners/default.asp |work=Bauer Consumer Media Ltd. |date=25 February 2010 |accessdate=11 January 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121113202012/http://www.empireonline.com/awards2009/winners/default.asp |archive-date=13 November 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Jameson Empire Awards Announce 2010 Nominees |url=http://www.bauermedia.co.uk/Press-Office/News/Jameson-Empire-Awards-Announce-2010-Nominees |work=Bauer Consumer Media Ltd. |date=25 February 2010 |accessdate=2 May 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100227045521/http://www.bauermedia.co.uk/Press-Office/News/Jameson-Empire-Awards-Announce-2010-Nominees/ |archivedate=27 February 2010  }}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, he earned nominations from [[AACTA Awards|Australian Academy Awards]] (AACTA) and [[Canadian Screen Awards]] for his performances in ''[[The Rover (2014 film)|The Rover]]'' and ''[[Maps to the Stars]]'' respectively.<ref name=\"aacta\">{{cite news|title=4TH AACTA AWARDS NOMINEES|url=http://www.aacta.org/media/249803/4th%20aacta%20awards%20nominees_all_by%20category.pdf|accessdate=3 December 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150503054801/http://www.aacta.org/media/249803/4th%20aacta%20awards%20nominees_all_by%20category.pdf|archivedate=3 May 2015}}</ref><ref>[https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/canadian-screen-awards-unveil-nominations-763287 \"Canadian Screen Awards Unveil Nominations\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150216152125/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/canadian-screen-awards-unveil-nominations-763287 |date=16 February 2015 }}. [[The Hollywood Reporter]], 15 January 2015.</ref> He won [[2015 Deauville American Film Festival#Awards|Hollywood Rising Star Award]] for his performance in film ''[[Life (2015 film)|Life]]'' from [[Deauville American Film Festival]] in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/robert-pattinson-elizabeth-olsen-be-817061|title=Robert Pattinson, Elizabeth Olsen to Be Honored at Deauville Film Fest|accessdate=24 August 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151211005914/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/robert-pattinson-elizabeth-olsen-be-817061|archive-date=11 December 2015|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2018, Robert Pattinson received a top award at the closing of the 53rd edition of the [[Karlovy Vary International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/robert-pattinson-get-karlovy-vary-honor-1123561|title=The 'Harry Potter' and 'Twilight' star will receive the President's Award at the festival's closing-night gala July 7.|accessdate=27 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627143059/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/robert-pattinson-get-karlovy-vary-honor-1123561|archive-date=27 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Honours===\nA wax statue of Pattinson was added to the [[Madame Tussauds]] collection in London and New York City in 2010.<ref>{{cite web |title= Robert Pattinson to join Madame Tussauds |url= http://www.madametussauds.com/London/NewsAndEvents/RobertPattinsonAnnounce |publisher= Merlin Entertainment Group |website= MadameTussauds.com |accessdate= 2 May 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100508155244/http://www.madametussauds.com/London/NewsAndEvents/RobertPattinsonAnnounce/ |archivedate= 8 May 2010 |df= dmy-all }}</ref> Pattinson along with his Twilight co-stars, Kristen Stewart and Taylor Lautner put his signature, hand and foot prints in wet concrete at [[Grauman's Chinese Theatre]] on 3 November 2011.<ref>{{cite web |title='Breaking Dawn' stars leave handprints, footprints in Hollywood |url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/gossip/2011/11/kristen-stewart-robert-pattinson-taylor-lautner-hand-footprint.html |work=LA Times |date=3 November 2011 |accessdate=2 October 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006232658/http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/gossip/2011/11/kristen-stewart-robert-pattinson-taylor-lautner-hand-footprint.html |archive-date=6 October 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 19 February 2014, Russian astronomer Timur Kryachko named an [[asteroid]] he had discovered after Pattinson, as ''246789 Pattinson''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Russian Astronomer Names Asteroid After 'Twilight' Actor|url=http://en.ria.ru/science/20140220/187716623/Russian-Astronomer-Names-Asteroid-After-Twilight-Actor.html|work=en.ria.ru|accessdate=20 February 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223031250/http://en.ria.ru/science/20140220/187716623/Russian-Astronomer-Names-Asteroid-After-Twilight-Actor.html|archive-date=23 February 2014|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Russia astronomer names asteroid after \"Twilight Saga\" vampire Pattinson|url=http://voiceofrussia.com/news/2014_02_20/Russia-astronomer-names-asteroid-after-Twilight-Saga-vampire-Pattinson-1750|work=[[Voice of Russia]]|accessdate=20 February 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140226114927/http://voiceofrussia.com/news/2014_02_20/Russia-astronomer-names-asteroid-after-Twilight-Saga-vampire-Pattinson-1750/|archive-date=26 February 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nHe was honoured with a tribute at 2017 Deauville American Film Festival on 2 September 2017, with screening of selected films of his during the festival run.<ref>{{cite web|title=Robert Pattinson, Woody Harrelson to Get Deauville Festival Honors|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/robert-pattinson-woody-harrelson-get-deauville-festival-honors-1031511|last=Rhonda|first=Richford|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=7 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170822110542/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/robert-pattinson-woody-harrelson-get-deauville-festival-honors-1031511|archive-date=22 August 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n<!-- Please note: do NOT use \"rowspans\" per WP:FILMOGRAPHY -->\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes works that have not yet been released\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n!scope=\"col\"| Year\n!scope=\"col\"| Title\n!scope=\"col\"| Role\n!scope=\"col\"| Di